symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.AccordionSection
symbols.description: Represents a panel which is a container for other controls. The container does not have any layout function.

properties.name: maxHeight
properties.description: When the section content exceeds maxHeight, a vertical scroll bar appears.

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: It is required that the used theme supports the control.

properties.name: collapsed
properties.description: It is recommended to adjust the settings for the width when the section is set to 'collapsed'.

properties.name: title
properties.description: Text for the section header

aggregations.name: content
aggregations.description:
Aggregates the controls that are contained in the panel. The control layout is browser-dependent.
For a stable content layout, use a layout control as direct single child.
When the panel dimensions are set, the child control may have width and height of 100%;
when the panel dimensions are not set, the child defines the panel size.

events.name: scroll
events.description: Event is fired when the user scrolls the panel

symbols.description: Textfield with list based text completion.

properties.name: enableScrolling
properties.description:
Determines whether scrolling should be enabled when the number of items is higher than maxPopupItems.
If set to false only the first n items (n=maxPopupItems) are shown.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.Button
symbols.description: Enables users to trigger actions such as save or print. For the button UI, you can define some text or an icon, or both.

properties.name: text
properties.description: Button text displayed at runtime.

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: Boolean property to enable the control (default is true). Buttons that are disabled have other colors than enabled ones, depending on custom settings.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Control width as common CSS-size (px or % as unit, for example)

properties.name: helpId
properties.description: Unique identifier used for help service

properties.name: icon
properties.description:
Icon to be displayed as graphical element within the button.
This can be an URI to an image or an icon font URI.

properties.name: iconHovered
properties.description:
Icon to be displayed as graphical element within the button when it is hovered (only if also a base icon was specified). If not specified the base icon is used.
If a icon font icon is used, this property is ignored.

properties.name: iconSelected
properties.description:
Icon to be displayed as graphical element within the button when it is selected (only if also a base icon was specified). If not specified the base or hovered icon is used.
If a icon font icon is used, this property is ignored.

properties.name: iconFirst
properties.description: If set to true (default), the display sequence is 1. icon 2. control text .

properties.name: height
properties.description: Specifies the button height. If this property is set, the height which is specified by the underlying theme is not used any longer.

properties.name: styled
properties.description: Indicates if the button is styled. If not it is rendered as native HTML-button. In this case a custom styling can be added usig addStyleClass.

properties.name: lite
properties.description: The button is rendered as lite button.

properties.name: style
properties.description:
Style of the button.
(e.g. emphasized)

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.DatePicker
symbols.description:
Allows end users to interact with dates.
Entries can directly be written in, or selected from a calendar pad.
Note: Dates can always be manually entered in the fix YYYYMMDD format, on top of the flexible "locale" format.
If the value is provided via data binding, using a Date.type the formatter of the Date.type is used.
Since version 1.22 the unified.Calendar is used inside the datePicker. So applications using the DatePicker should load the unified library. Otherwise it will be loaded the first time a DatePicker is opened.

Defines the date as a "yyyymmdd" string, independent from the format used. The inherited textField "value" attribute uses the date format as configured via the locale.
The date is interpreted as gregorian date

The API supports features such as popups with fixed sizes, popups with unlimited width, scrolling bars for large windows, and control nesting (for example, a drop-down list can be included in the window).

returnValue.description: indicates whether the dialog is currently enabled or not.

methods.description: Determines whether the dialog is currently enabled or not. Applications can't control the enabled state via a property. A dialog is implicitly enabled depending on its openState. Descendant controls that honor the enabled state of their ancestors will appear disabled after the dialog is closed.

experimental.text:
Whether a dialog is regarded as "enabled" during the state transitions (OPENING, CLOSING) is not fully decided. Currently, it is enabled during the OPENING phase and disabled during the CLOSING phase. The only potential change would be to treat the OPENING phase as disabled as well. Applications should be prepared to receive events from "enabled" controls after they called open() on the dialog until close() is called on it. If the mentioned potential change should happen, the dialog will become enabled only after the transition to OPEN. Events from "enabled" children then can still only arrive between open() and close(), so applications that obey the previous rule should continue to work. Only end users or code that explicitly triggers pseudo user events will notice a difference.
A second aspect that might change is the visual behavior of the content: during the CLOSING phase it 'looks' enabled but in fact it is already disabled. This avoids unnecessary redraws for content that becomes hidden soon. Should this show to be confusing for end users, it might be changed.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.Image
symbols.description:
A wrapper around the IMG tag. The image can be loaded from a remote or local server.
There are various size setting options available, and the images can be combined with actions.

properties.name: src
properties.description: Relative or absolute path to URL where the image file is stored.

properties.name: width
properties.description: When the empty value is kept, the original size is not changed. It is also possible to make settings for width or height only, the overall size is maintained then, considering the aspect ratio.

properties.name: height
properties.description: When the empty value is kept, the original size is not changed. It is also possible to make settings for width or height only, the overall size is maintained then, considering the aspect ratio.

properties.name: decorative
properties.description:
A decorative image is included for design reasons. Accessibility tools will ignore decorative images.
Note: If the Image has an image map (useMap is set), this property will be overridden (the image will not be rendered as decorative).
A decorative image has no ALT attribute, so the Alt property is ignored if the image is decorative.

properties.name: alt
properties.description:
The alternative text that is displayed in case the Image is not available, or cannot be displayed.
If the image is set to decorative this property is ignored.

properties.name: useMap
properties.description: The name of the image map that defines the clickable areas

symbols.description: The InPlaceEdit is a functionality to have text in display mode that can be changed in place.

properties.name: valueState
properties.description:
Visualizes warnings or errors related to the InPlaceEdit. Possible values: Warning, Error, Success.
If the content control has a own valueState property this will be used.

properties.name: undoEnabled
properties.description: If undo is enabled after changing the text an undo button appears.

properties.name: design
properties.description:
Defines the visual appearance of the control.
Currently this is not supported for Labels.

aggregations.name: content
aggregations.description:
Content control of the InPlaceEdit.
The following controls are allowed:
TextField, ComboBox, DropdownBox and Link

events.name: change
events.description: Event is fired when the text in the field has changed AND the focus leaves the InPlaceEdit or the Enter key is pressed.

Callers that are only interested in tooltips of type string (e.g. to render them as a title attribute), should call the convenience method {@link #getTooltip_AsString} instead. symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.Label
symbols.description: The control is used for labeling other controls. The API provides formatting options, for example, for bold display or alignment. A label can have an icon.

properties.name: design
properties.description: Defines whether the labels are in bold format.

properties.name: textDirection
properties.description: Determines the text direction - right-to-left (RTL) and left-to-right (LTR).

properties.name: wrapping
properties.description: Specifies whether a line wrapping width shall be displayed when the text value is longer than the width is.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Determines the control width as common CSS-size (for example, px or % as unit).

properties.name: text
properties.description: Determines the text to be displayed.

properties.name: icon
properties.description:
Determines the icon to be displayed in the control.
This can be an URI to an image or an icon font URI.

properties.name: textAlign
properties.description: Determines the alignment of the text. Available options are Begin, Center, End, Left, and Right.

properties.name: required
properties.description:
Allows to enforce the required indicator even when the associated control doesn't have a getRequired method (a required property) or when the flag is not set.
If the associated control has a required property, the values of both required flags are combined with the OR operator, so a Label can't override a required=true value.

properties.name: requiredAtBegin
properties.description: Determines whether the required indicator is at the beginning of the label (if set) or at the end (if not set).

associations.name: labelFor
associations.description:
Defines the association to the labeled control.
By default, the label is set the for the attribute to the ID of the labeled control.
This can be changed with the implementation of function getIdForLabel on the labelled control.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.layout.BorderLayout
symbols.description:
Based upon the border layout as it comes with the Java standard. Using this layout, you are able to divide your available UI space into five areas whose sizes can be defined. These areas are: Top: Header; Bottom: Footer; Begin: Left/right-hand side panel; Center: Content area
in the middle; End: Right/left-hand side panel.

properties.name: rtl
properties.description: The RTL setting swaps the areas Begin and End. Since version 1.5.2, this property is deprecated and ignored as it conflicts with the central configuration for the page.

deprecated.text: RTL should not be configured on control level but is determined by a global configuration.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.layout.MatrixLayout
symbols.description:
A matrix layout arranges controls in a grid structure, using rows which need not have the same number of cells.

It uses predefined cell classes that guarantee appropriate distances between cells in the grid. The cell's vGutter property lets you specify additional horizontal distances easily. You can set these additional distances (known as gutters) with or without separators. The distance for each cell is specified by assigning a specific enumeration value of the class LayoutCellSeparator of the matrix data object.

You should avoid nesting matrix layouts. You should only use a matrix layout if you need to align controls horizontally across rows.

properties.name: width
properties.description:
CSS width of the matrix layout.
If the LayoutFixed = true a adequate width should be provided.

properties.name: height
properties.description: CSS height of the matrix layout.

properties.name: layoutFixed
properties.description:
Sets the table layout. If fixed the width parameter of a column has priority, if not the width of the content of the colums has priority.
The default is "fixed".
If the fixed layout is used a adequate width of the MatrixLayout should be provided. Otherwise the column width displayed could be different than the given ones because of browser dependend optimazations.

properties.name: columns
properties.description: Number of columns. If not specified, the number of columns will be determined from the given cells.

properties.name: widths
properties.description:
Widths of the columns. Use an array to define the widths of the columns.
If a column shall have an automatical sizing enter "auto" for this column width.

aggregations.name: rows
aggregations.description: The matrix layout's individual rows.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.layout.MatrixLayoutCell
symbols.description: Non-control element used as part of a matrix layout's inner structure.

properties.name: backgroundDesign
properties.description: Determines the matrix layout cell's background design.

properties.name: colSpan
properties.description:
Determines how many columns of the underlying grid structure are occupied
by this matrix layout cell.

properties.name: hAlign
properties.description:
Determines the horizontal alignment of the matrix layout cell's content
with the cell's borders.

properties.name: padding
properties.description:
Determines the padding of the matrix layout cell's content within the
cell's borders. The default value is appropriate for all cells in a
form-like layout. Consider to remove the padding on the outer layout in
case of nesting.

properties.name: rowSpan
properties.description:
Determines how many rows of the underlying grid structure are occupied by this matrix layout cell.
In case a row-height is used, all rows affected by the RowSpan must have the same unit.

properties.name: separation
properties.description:
Determines how a matrix layout cell is separated from its predecessor,
via a vertical gutter of variable width, with or without a vertical line.

properties.name: vAlign
properties.description:
Determines the vertical alignment of the matrix layout cell's content
with the cell's borders.

aggregations.name: content
aggregations.description:
The matrix layout cell's content (arbitrary controls).

If the matrix row has a defined height and the matrix has layoutFixed = true, the controls inside of a cell should all use the same unit for its height property.

methods.name: addStyleClass

parameters.name: sStyleClass
parameters.description: the CSS class name to be added

methods.description:
The string given as "sStyleClass" will be added to the "class" attribute of this element's root HTML element. This method is intended to be used to mark controls as being of a special type for which special styling can be provided using CSS selectors that reference this style class name. 
Example:
myButton.addStyleClass("myRedTextButton"); // add a CSS class to one button instance

...and in CSS:
.myRedTextButton {
color: red;
}
This will add the CSS class "myRedTextButton" to the Button HTML and the CSS code above will then make the text in this particular button red. Only characters allowed inside HTML attributes are allowed. Quotes are not allowed and this method will ignore any strings containing quotes. Strings containing spaces are interpreted as ONE custom style class (even though CSS selectors interpret them as different classes) and can only removed later by calling removeStyleClass() with exactly the same (space-containing) string as parameter. Multiple calls with the same sStyleClass will have no different effect than calling once. If sStyleClass is null, the call is ignored. Returns this to allow method chaining

methods.name: addStyleClass

parameters.name: sStyleClass
parameters.description: the CSS class name to be added

methods.description:
The string given as "sStyleClass" will be added to the "class" attribute of this element's root HTML element. This method is intended to be used to mark controls as being of a special type for which special styling can be provided using CSS selectors that reference this style class name. 
Example:
myButton.addStyleClass("myRedTextButton"); // add a CSS class to one button instance

...and in CSS:
.myRedTextButton {
color: red;
}
This will add the CSS class "myRedTextButton" to the Button HTML and the CSS code above will then make the text in this particular button red. Only characters allowed inside HTML attributes are allowed. Quotes are not allowed and this method will ignore any strings containing quotes. Strings containing spaces are interpreted as ONE custom style class (even though CSS selectors interpret them as different classes) and can only removed later by calling removeStyleClass() with exactly the same (space-containing) string as parameter. Multiple calls with the same sStyleClass will have no different effect than calling once. If sStyleClass is null, the call is ignored. Returns this to allow method chaining

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.layout.Padding
symbols.description:
Padding, e.g. of a layout cell's content within the cell's borders.
Note that all options except "None" include a padding of 2px at the top and
bottom, and differ only in the presence of a 4px padding towards the beginning
or end of a line, in the current locale's writing direction.

properties.name: Begin
properties.description:
Top and bottom padding of 2px.
Padding of 4px towards the beginning of a line, in the current locale's
writing direction, but none towards its end.

properties.name: Both
properties.description:
Top and bottom padding of 2px.
Padding of 4px towards both the beginning and end of a line.

properties.name: End
properties.description:
Top and bottom padding of 2px.
Padding of 4px towards the end of a line, in the current locale's
writing direction, but none towards its beginning.

properties.name: Neither
properties.description:
Top and bottom padding of 2px.
No padding towards neither the beginning nor end of a line.

properties.name: None
properties.description: No padding at all.

Provides an absolute or relative reference to an internal or external URL. The classical target parameters are supported.
Another usage scenario is triggering an action, for example to open a popup window. In both cases, the link is a hypertext link.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.ListBox
symbols.description:
Provides a list of items from which users can choose an item.
For the design of the list box, features such as defining the list box height, fixing the number of visible items,
choosing one item to be the item that is marked by default when the list box is shown,
or a scroll bar for large list boxes are available.

properties.name: editable
properties.description:
Determines whether the ListBox is interactive or not.
Can be used to disable interaction with mouse or keyboard.

properties.name: enabled
properties.description:
Determines whether the ListBox is enabled or not.
Can be used to disable interaction with mouse or keyboard.
Disabled controls have another color display depending on custom settings.

properties.name: allowMultiSelect
properties.description: Determines whether multiple selection is allowed.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Control width as common CSS-size (px or % as unit, for example).

properties.name: height
properties.description:
Control height as common CSS-size (px or % as unit, for example).
The setting overrides any definitions made for the setVisibleItems() method.

properties.name: scrollTop
properties.description:
Scroll bar position from the top.
Setting the scrollTop property and calling scrollToIndex are two operations
influencing the same "physical" property, so the last call "wins".

properties.name: displayIcons
properties.description:
Determines whether the icons of the list items shall also be displayed.
Enabling icons requires some space to be reserved for them.
Displaying icons can also influence the width and height of a single item,
which affects the overall height of the ListBox when defined in number of items.
Note that the number of icons that can be displayed in the ListBox depends on the
size of the icons themselves and of the total ListBox height.

properties.name: displaySecondaryValues
properties.description: Determines whether the text values from the additionalText property (see sap.ui.core.ListItems) shall be displayed.

properties.name: valueTextAlign
properties.description: Determines the text alignment in the primary ListBox column.

properties.name: secondaryValueTextAlign
properties.description: Determines the text alignment in the secondary ListBox text column (if available).

properties.name: minWidth
properties.description: Determines the minimum width of the ListBox. If not set, there is no minimum width.

properties.name: maxWidth
properties.description: Determines the maximum width of the ListBox. If not set, there is no maximum width.

properties.name: visibleItems
properties.description:
The ListBox height in number of items that are initially displayed without scrolling.
This setting overwrites height settings in terms of CSS size that have been made.
When the items have different heights, the height of the first item is used for all
other item height calculations.
Note that if there are one or more separators between the visible ListBox items,
the displayed items might not relate 1:1 to the initially specified number of items.
When the value is retrieved, it equals the previously set value if it was set;
otherwise, it will be the number of items completely fitting into the ListBox without
scrolling in the case the control was already rendered.
Note that if the control was not rendered, the behavior will be undefined,
it may return -1 or any other number.

aggregations.name: items
aggregations.description: Aggregation of items to be displayed. Must be either of type sap.ui.core.ListItem or sap.ui.core.SeparatorItem.

associations.name: ariaDescribedBy
associations.description: Association to controls / ids which describe this control (see WAI-ARIA attribute aria-describedby).

associations.name: ariaLabelledBy
associations.description: Association to controls / ids which label this control (see WAI-ARIA attribute aria-labelledby).

selectedIndex.description:
The currently selected index of the ListBox.
In the case of multiple selection, this is exactly one of the selected indices -
the one whose selection has triggered the selection change.
To get all currently selected indices, use selectedIndices.

selectedItem.name: selectedItem
selectedItem.description:
The currently selected item of the ListBox.
In the case of multiple selection, this is exactly one of the selected items -
the one whose selection has triggered the selection change.

selectedIndices.name: selectedIndices
selectedIndices.description: Array containing the indices which are selected.

parameters.description: If set to true, the ListBox only scrolls if the item is not completely visible, and it scrolls for exactly the space to make it fully visible. If set to false, the item is scrolled to the top position (if possible).

methods.description:
If the ListBox has a scroll bar because the number of items is larger than the number of visible items,
this method scrolls to the item with the given index.
If there are enough items, this item will then appear at the topmost visible position in the ListBox.
If bLazy is true, it only scrolls as far as required to make the item visible.
Setting the scrollTop property and calling scrollToIndex are two operations
influencing the same "physical" property, so the last call "wins".

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.Menu
symbols.description:
A menu is an interactive element which provides a choice of different actions to the user. These actions (items) can also be organized in submenus.
Like other dialog-like controls, the menu is not rendered within the control hierarchy. Instead it can be opened at a specified position via a function call.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.MenuBar
symbols.description:
Represents a user interface area which is the entry point for menus with their menu items. MenuBar is useful for applications which shall offer a
set of actions that shall be provided in a structured way. The MenuBar contains the menu titles from where users navigate to the single items. The control supports
for example long menu item texts, automated scrolling for menu items when the browser space is not large enough to display all items, defining images for single
or all items in a menu, automated layouting of items with or w/o image, and active/non-active items.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.MessageBox

methods.name: alert

parameters.name: vMessage
parameters.description: Message to be displayed in the alert box

parameters.name: fnCallback
parameters.description: callback function to be called when the user closed the dialog

parameters.name: sTitle
parameters.description: Title to be displayed in the alert box

parameters.name: sDialogId
parameters.description: ID to be used for the alert box. Intended for test scenarios, not recommended for productive apps

methods.description:
Displays an alert box with the given message and an OK button (no icons). If a callback is given, it is called after the alert box has been closed by the user via the OK button or via the Close icon. The callback is called with the following signature: 
  function ()
The alert box opened by this method is modal and it is processed asynchronously. Applications have to use the fnCallback to continue work after the user closed the alert box.

methods.name: confirm

parameters.name: vMessage
parameters.description: Message to display

parameters.name: fnCallback
parameters.description: Callback to be called

parameters.name: sTitle
parameters.description: Title to display

parameters.name: sDialogId
parameters.description: ID to be used for the confirmation dialog. Intended for test scenarios, not recommended for productive apps

methods.description:
Displays a confirmation dialog box with the given message, a question icon, an OK button, and a Cancel button. If a callback is given, it is called after the alert box has been closed by the user via one of the buttons or via the close icon. The callback is called with the following signature 
  function(bConfirmed)
where bConfirmed is set to true when the user has activated the OK button. The confirmation dialog box opened by this method is modal and it is processed asynchronously. Applications have to use the fnCallback to continue work after the user closed the alert box.

methods.name: show

parameters.name: vMessage
parameters.description: The message to be displayed.

parameters.name: oIcon
parameters.description: The icon to be displayed.

parameters.name: sTitle
parameters.description: The title of the message box.

parameters.name: vActions
parameters.description:
Either a single action, or an array of actions.
     If no action(s) are given, the single action MessageBox.Action.OK is taken as a default for the parameter.

parameters.name: fnCallback
parameters.description: Function to be called when the user has pressed a button or has closed the message box.

parameters.name: oDefaultAction
parameters.description: Must be one of the actions provided in vActions.

parameters.name: sDialogId
parameters.description: ID to be used for the dialog. Intended for test scenarios, not recommended for productive apps

methods.description: Creates and displays a simple message box with the given text and buttons, and optionally other parts. After the user has selected a button or closed the message box using the close icon, the callback function is invoked when given. The only mandatory parameter is vMessage. Either a string with the corresponding text or even a layout control could be provided. The created dialog box is executed asynchronously. When it has been created and registered for rendering, this function returns without waiting for a user reaction. When applications have to react on the users choice, they have to provide a callback function and postpone any reaction on the user choice until that callback is triggered. The signature of the callback is function (oAction); where oAction is the button that the user has pressed. When the user has pressed the close button, a MessageBox.Action.Close is returned.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.MessageBox.Action
symbols.description:
Enumeration of supported actions in a MessageBox.

Each action is represented as a button in the message box. The values of this enumeration are used for both,
specifying the set of allowed actions as well as reporting back the user choice.

properties.name: ABORT
properties.description: Adds an "Abort" button to the message box.

properties.name: CANCEL
properties.description: Adds a "Cancel" button to the message box.

properties.name: CLOSE
properties.description: Adds a "Close" button to the message box.

properties.name: IGNORE
properties.description: Adds an "Ignore" button to the message box.

properties.name: NO
properties.description: Adds a "No" button to the message box.

properties.name: OK
properties.description: Adds an "Ok" button to the message box.

properties.name: RETRY
properties.description: Adds a "Retry" button to the message box.

properties.name: YES
properties.description: Adds a "Yes" button to the message box.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.MessageBox.Icon
symbols.description: Enumeration of the pre-defined icons that can be used in a MessageBox.

properties.name: CRITICAL
properties.description: Shows the critical error icon in the message box.

deprecated.text: The error icon is used instead

properties.name: ERROR
properties.description: Shows the error icon in the message box.

properties.name: INFORMATION
properties.description: Shows the information icon in the message box.

properties.name: NONE
properties.description: Shows no icon in the message box.

properties.name: QUESTION
properties.description: Shows the question icon in the message box.

properties.name: SUCCESS
properties.description: Shows the success icon in the message box.

properties.name: WARNING
properties.description: Shows the warning icon in the message box.

symbols.description: Provides navigation between pages within a list of numbered pages.

properties.name: currentPage
properties.description: Represents the current page (first page has index 1, not 0, to match the visual number)

properties.description: Represents the overall number of pages that are embedded into the parent control

events.name: page
events.description: Event is fired when the user navigates to another page by selecting it directly, or by jumping forward/backward.

srcPage.name: srcPage
srcPage.description: The page which is the current one before the page event is fired (and another page is displayed)

targetPage.name: targetPage
targetPage.description:
The page that shall be displayed next after the page event is fired.

The page number is 1-based: the first page has index 1, not 0, to match the number visible in the UI.

type.description:
Provides the values 'First', 'Last', 'Next', 'Previous', 'Goto'. The event parameter informs the application
how the user navigated to the new page: Whether the 'Next' button was used, or another button, or whether the page was directly
selected

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.Panel
symbols.description:
Represents a container with scroll functionality, that can be used for text and controls.
The Panel does not layout the embedded controls.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Determines the width of the Panel in CSS size.

properties.name: height
properties.description:
Determines the height of the Panel in CSS size.
Per default, the height for the Panel is automatically adjusted to the content.
Dimension allows to explicitly specify the height.

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: Represents the state of the of the Panel (enabled or disabled)

properties.name: scrollLeft
properties.description: Determines the scroll position from left to right. Value "0" means leftmost position.

properties.name: scrollTop
properties.description: Determines the scroll position from top to bottom. Value "0" means topmost position.

properties.name: applyContentPadding
properties.description:
Determines whether the Panel will have padding.
Padding is theme-dependent.

properties.name: collapsed
properties.description:
Determines whether the Panel will be initially collapsed.
When it is initially collapsed, the contents are not rendered.
A collapsed Panel consumes less space than an expanded one.

properties.name: areaDesign
properties.description:
Determines the background color.
Note that color settings are theme-dependent.

properties.name: borderDesign
properties.description:
Determines if the Panel can have a box as border.
Note that displaying borders is theme-dependent.

properties.name: showCollapseIcon
properties.description: Determines whether the Panel will have an icon for collapsing/expanding, or not.

properties.name: text
properties.description:
Specifies the text that is rendered in the Panel header.
Can be used to create a simple titles that do not require an icon in the header.

aggregations.name: content
aggregations.description:
Aggregates the controls that are contained in the Panel.
It is recommended to use a layout control as single direct child.
When the Panel dimensions are set, the child control may have width and height of 100%.
When the dimensions are not set, the child defines the size of the Panel.

aggregations.name: title
aggregations.description:
Aggregates the title element of the Panel.
For text titles only, you alternatively could use setText() which also creates a title in the background.

aggregations.name: buttons
aggregations.description: The buttons that shall be displayed in the Panel header

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.ProgressIndicator
symbols.description:
Shows the progress of a process in a graphical way.
The indicator can be displayed with or without numerical values.
The filling can be displayed in color only, or additionally with the percentage rate.
The indicator status can be interactive.

Determines whether the control is enabled or not.
Disabled controls have different colors, and can not be focused.

Determines the color of the bar which visualizes the progress.
Possible values defined in the sap.ui.core.BarColor enumeration are the following:
CRITICAL (yellow), NEGATIVE (red), POSITIVE (green), NEUTRAL (blue) (default value).

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.RadioButton
symbols.description:
RadioButton is a control similar to CheckBox, but it allows the user to choose only one of the predefined set of options.

Usually, RadioButton is used in a group with other RadioButtons (with the groupName property or by using
sap.ui.commons.RadioButtonGroup), thus providing a limited choice for the user. An event is triggered when
the user makes a change of the selection.

properties.name: text
properties.description: Defines the text displayed next to the RadioButton.

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: Displays the disabled controls in another color, depending on the customer settings.

properties.name: editable
properties.description: Specifies whether the user can select the RadioButton.

properties.name: selected
properties.description: Specifies the select state of the RadioButton.

properties.name: valueState
properties.description: Enumeration sap.ui.core.ValueState provides state values Error, Success, Warning and None.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Determines the control width. By default, it depends on the text length. Alternatively, CSS sizes in % or px can be set.

properties.name: textDirection
properties.description:
Defines the text direction - options are left-to-right (LTR) and right-to-left (RTL). Alternatively, the control can
inherit the text direction from its parent container.

properties.name: groupName
properties.description:
Defines the name of the RadioButtonGroup, in which the current RadioButton belongs to. You can define a new name for
the group. If no new name is specified, the default is sapUiRbDefaultGroup. By default, when one of the RadioButtons
in a group is selected, all others are unselected.

properties.name: key
properties.description: Can be used for subsequent actions.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.RadioButtonGroup
symbols.description:
The RadioButtonGroup is a basic control that is used to provide area for making interactive
choice out of a set of options. It represents a list with items where exactly one item can
be selected in a session. For the representation of the single group entries, the RadioButton
items are created automatically. For the RadioButton choice, mouse and keyboard navigation
usage is supported.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Defines the width of the RadioButtonGroup.

properties.name: columns
properties.description: Determines the maximum number of RadioButtons displayed in one line.

properties.name: editable
properties.description:
Specifies whether the user can change the selected value of the RadioButtonGroup.
When the property is set to false, the control obtains visual styles
different from its visual styles for the normal and the disabled state.
Additionally the control is no longer interactive, but can receive focus.

properties.name: valueState
properties.description:
he value state to be displayed for the RadioButton. Possible values are: sap.ui.core.ValueState.Error,
sap.ui.core.ValueState.Warning, sap.ui.core.ValueState.Success and sap.ui.core.ValueState.None.
Note: Setting this attribute to sap.ui.core.ValueState.Error when the accessibility feature is enabled,
sets the value of the invalid property for the whole RadioButtonGroup to true.

properties.name: selectedIndex
properties.description: The index of the selected/checked RadioButton.

properties.name: enabled
properties.description:
Enables/disables the RadioButtonGroup. If it is disabled all RadioButtons will be displayed as disabled.
The enabled property of the Item will not be used in this case. If the RadioButtonGroup is enabled, the
enabled property of the Item will define if a RadioButton is enabled or not.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.RatingIndicator
symbols.description:
RatingIndicator is used to let the user do some rating on a given topic. The amount of
rating symbols can be specified, as well as the URIs to the image icons which shall be
used as rating symbols. When the user performs a rating, an event is fired.

properties.name: editable
properties.description: Determines if the rating symbols can be edited.

properties.name: maxValue
properties.description: Determines the number of displayed rating symbols

properties.name: value
properties.description:
Determines the currently selected value. If value is set to sap.ui.commons.RatingIndicator.NoValue,
the averageValue is shown.

properties.name: averageValue
properties.description:
Determines the average value. This value is shown if no value is set.
This can be used to display an average Value before the user votes.

properties.name: iconSelected
properties.description:
The URI to the image which shall be displayed for all selected rating symbols.
Note that when this attribute is used, also the other icon attributes need to be set.

properties.name: iconUnselected
properties.description:
The URI to the image which shall be displayed for all unselected rating symbols.
If this attribute is used, a requirement is that all custom icons need to have the same size.
Note that when this attribute is used also the other icon attributes need to be set.

properties.name: iconHovered
properties.description:
The URI to the image which is displayed when the mouse hovers onto a rating symbol.
If used, a requirement is that all custom icons need to have the same size.
Note that when this attribute is used also the other icon attributes need to be set.

properties.name: visualMode
properties.description:
Defines how float values are visualized: Full, Half, Continuous
(see enumeration RatingIndicatorVisualMode)

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.SearchField
symbols.description: Allows the user to type search queries and to trigger the search. Optionally, suggestions can be added.

properties.name: enableListSuggest
properties.description: Defines whether a pop up list shall be provided for suggestions

properties.name: showListExpander
properties.description: Defines whether the list expander shall be displayed in the case of an enabled list for suggestions. This feature is deactivated on mobile devices.

properties.name: enableClear
properties.description: Defines whether the clear functionality shall be active

properties.name: showExternalButton
properties.description: Defines whether an additional search button shall be displayed

properties.name: enableCache
properties.description: When list suggestion is enabled all suggestions are cached and no suggest event is fired.

properties.name: enableFilterMode
properties.description: Defines whether the search event should also be fired when the SearchField is empty (like a Filter field) and when the clear button (if activated) is pressed.

properties.name: value
properties.description: Text that shall be displayed within the search field

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: Disabled fields have different colors, and they can not be focused.

properties.name: editable
properties.description: Non-editable controls have different colors, depending on custom settings

properties.name: width
properties.description: Control width in CSS-size

properties.name: maxLength
properties.description: Maximum number of characters. Value '0' means the feature is switched off.

properties.name: valueState
properties.description: Visualizes warnings or errors related to the input field. Possible values: Warning, Error, Success, None.

properties.name: placeholder
properties.description: Placeholder for the input field.

properties.name: textAlign
properties.description: Sets the horizontal alignment of the text

properties.name: visibleItemCount
properties.description:
Defines the number of items in the suggestion list that shall be displayed at once. If the overall number of list items is higher than the setting,
a scroll bar is provided.

properties.name: startSuggestion
properties.description: Minimum length of the entered string triggering the suggestion list.

properties.name: maxSuggestionItems
properties.description: Maximum number of suggestion items in the suggestion list.

properties.name: maxHistoryItems
properties.description:
Maximum number of history items in the suggestion list.
0 displays and stores no history. The history is locally stored on the client. Therefore do not activate this feature when this control handles confidential data.

aggregations.name: searchProvider
aggregations.description: Search provider instance which handles the suggestions for this SearchField (e.g. Open Search Protocol).

associations.description: Association to controls / IDs which describe this control (see WAI-ARIA attribute aria-describedby).

associations.name: ariaLabelledBy
associations.description: Association to controls / IDs which label this control (see WAI-ARIA attribute aria-labelledby).

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.Slider
symbols.description:
The interactive control is displayed either as a horizontal or a vertical line with a pointer and units of measurement.
Users can move the pointer along the line to change values with graphical support.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Width of the horizontal slider.

properties.name: min
properties.description: Minimal value of the slider. Note: If min is larger than max both values will be switched

properties.name: max
properties.description: Maximal value of the slider Note: If min is larger than max both values will be switched

properties.name: value
properties.description: Current value of the slider. (Position of the grip.) Note: If the value is not in the valid range (between min and max) it will be changed to be in the valid range.

properties.name: smallStepWidth
properties.description: The grip can only be moved in steps of this width.

properties.name: totalUnits
properties.description: Number of units that are displayed by ticks. The PageUp and PageDown keys navigate according to these units.

properties.name: stepLabels
properties.description: Display step numbers for the ticks on the slider.

properties.name: editable
properties.description: Using the slider interactively requires value "true".

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: Switches enabled state of the control. Disabled fields have different colors, and can not be focused.

properties.name: labels
properties.description: Labels to be displayed instead of numbers. Attribute totalUnits and label count should be the same Note: To show the labels stepLabels must be activated.

properties.name: vertical
properties.description: Orientation of slider

properties.name: height
properties.description: Height of the vertical slider.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.Splitter
symbols.description: Allows to split the screen into two areas. Make sure that the container for the splitter has an absolute height or set an absolute height for the splitter using the height property. Otherwise the height of the splitter is calculated by the height of its contents.

properties.name: splitterOrientation
properties.description: The splitter can have horizontal or vertical orientation.

properties.name: splitterPosition
properties.description:
Position of splitter bar in percentage.
The default value means that the splitter is positioned in the middle of the area that is available for the splitter.

properties.name: minSizeFirstPane

TabStrip represents a container for tab controls, which contain the content and generally other controls.
The user switches between the tabs to display the content.

parameters.description: The index of the tab that should be closed

methods.description:
Closes a tab (if the tab is selected, the next one will be selected;
if it's the last tab, the previous one will be selected).

This method should be called if the close event is fired.
It can not be called automatically because the consumer might need to run some logic before the tab is closed.

properties.description: Number of Columns. Cols means number of characters per row. This proprty is only used if Width is not used.

properties.name: rows
properties.description: Number of Rows. This proprty is only used if Height is not used.

properties.name: wrapping
properties.description: Text wrapping. Possible values are: Soft, Hard, Off.

properties.description: Position of cursor, e.g., to let the user re-start typing at the same position as before the server roundtrip

properties.name: value

properties.description: Direction of the text. Possible values: "rtl", "ltr".

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: Switches enabled state of the control. Disabled fields have different colors, and can not be focused.

properties.name: editable
properties.description: Switches edit state of the control. Read-only fields have different colors, depending on theme setting.

properties.name: required
properties.description: Depending on theme the TextField is shown as required. If a Label is assigned to the TextField it will visualize the requires state too.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Width of text field. When it is set (CSS-size such as % or px), this is the exact size. When left blank, the text field length defines the width.

properties.name: maxLength
properties.description: Maximum number of characters. Value '0' means the feature is switched off.

properties.name: valueState
properties.description: Visualizes warnings or errors related to the text field. Possible values: Warning, Error, Success.

properties.name: textAlign
properties.description: Sets the horizontal alignment of the text.

properties.name: imeMode
properties.description: State of the Input Method Editor (IME).

properties.description: Font type. valid values are Standard and Monospace.

properties.description: Unique identifier used for help service.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.ToolbarDesign
symbols.description: Determines the visual design of a Toolbar.

properties.name: Flat
properties.description: The included controls have a very light appearance. The feature might be not supported by all themes.

properties.name: Standard
properties.description:
The toolbar elements such as buttons for example have their normal visual design, and the toolbar appears solid.
The feature might be not supported by all themes.

properties.name: Transparent
properties.description:
The controls included in the toolbar have a normal visual design where the toolbar appears transparent.
The feature might be not supported by all themes.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.ToolbarItem
symbols.description:
Marker interface for common controls which are suitable for use within a toolbar.
The most prominent example of a toolbar item is a button which is mostly used with
an icon instead of a text caption.

Toolbar items must have a fixed height compatible with the toolbar being
a single horizontal row. They can refer to the toolbar's marker class
"sapUiTb" to adjust their own theming when used inside a toolbar.

symbols.name: sap.ui.commons.TriStateCheckBox
symbols.description:
TriStateCheckBox to reflect mixed state for checkboxes. The control can display three states, namely checked, unchecked and mixed. However, mixed state cannot be directly reached by user interaction on the particular control.
It can be only set by the control's public toggle function, to make a behaviour possible which is e.g. required in checkbox trees.

properties.name: selectionState
properties.description: Defines the states of the checkbox

properties.name: text
properties.description: Defines the text displayed next to the check box

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: Using this property, the control could be disabled, if required.

properties.name: editable
properties.description: Specifies whether the user shall be allowed to flag the check box

properties.name: valueState
properties.description: Accepts the core enumeration ValueState.type that supports 'None', 'Error', 'Warning' and 'Success'.

properties.name: width
properties.description: The width can be set to an absolute value. If no value is set, the control width results from the text length.

properties.name: textDirection
properties.description: The value can be set to LTR or RTL. Otherwise, the control inherits the text direction from its parent control.

events.name: change
events.description: Event is triggered when the control status is changed by the user by flagging or unflagging the checkbox.

selectionState.description: Checks whether the box is flagged or not flagged.

If an icon font icon is used, this property is ignored.

methods.name: getIconDisabledURL

returnValue.description: Value of property iconDisabledURL

methods.description: Gets current value of property iconDisabledURL. URL of the icon for the value help when disabled. If no parameter is supplied the default icon image will be shown. If an icon font icon is used, this property is ignored.

methods.name: getIconHoverURL

returnValue.description: Value of property iconHoverURL

methods.description: Gets current value of property iconHoverURL. URL of the icon for the value help when hovered. If no parameter is supplied the standard icon image will be shown. If an icon font icon is used, this property is ignored.

methods.name: getIconURL

returnValue.description: Value of property iconURL

methods.description: Gets current value of property iconURL. URL of the standard icon for the value help. If no parameter is supplied the default icon image will be shown. This can be an URI to an image or an icon font URI.

parameters.name: sIconDisabledURL
parameters.description: New value for property iconDisabledURL

methods.description: Sets a new value for property iconDisabledURL. URL of the icon for the value help when disabled. If no parameter is supplied the default icon image will be shown. If an icon font icon is used, this property is ignored. When called with a value of null or undefined, the default value of the property will be restored.
